main event: On January 11, 1961, a reddish-white object was observed at high speed, initially identified as the planet Venus.
interesting points: The sighting was made from Fairborn, Ohio., The object appeared reddish-white and was reported moving at high speed., The observer classified it at times as resembling an aircraft., The object was thought to be a disc-shaped or cylinder-shaped object larger than conventional aircraft., The sighting of the object was intermittent throughout the observation period.
witness description: Major W. Rosen described the sighting.
